Time Series Figures

Average CPUE by month by effort group, 2012–2017.

Defining CPUE. This is going to be an important difference that I don’t see a way to resolve. Chan (2020) defines catch as ALL fish KEPT (mahi-mahi, marlin, etc.). The version of the observer dataset that I have only has data on bigeye, yellowfin, albacore, skipjack, bluefin, unidentified tuna, and swordfish. Let’s combine all of those and divide them by 1,000 hooks to get a “comparable” measure of CPUE. The majority of these species are kept.

NOAA.subset$all.fish <- NOAA.subset$count_bigeye_tuna + NOAA.subset$count_yellowfin_tuna + NOAA.subset$count_albacore_tuna + NOAA.subset$count_skipjack_tuna + NOAA.subset$count_bluefin_tuna + NOAA.subset$count_unid_tuna + NOAA.subset$count_swordfish
NOAA.subset$all.fish.cpue <- (NOAA.subset$all.fish/NOAA.subset$num_hks_set)*1000

# Now it's time to collapse the data and see what happens

trip.level <- aggregate(cbind(revenue_day,PMNM_dummy, high_post, high_effort, trip_days) ~ trip_id + vessel_id,data = subset(final.trip.vessel, medium_effort==0 & trip_days>0),mean)
trip.level$revenue_trip <- trip.level$revenue_day*trip.level$trip_days

controls <- subset(final.trip.vessel, select = c("trip_id","year","month","NE","SE","NW","CW","SW","deep_set","last_date"))

trip.level <- merge(controls,trip.level, by = "trip_id", all.y=TRUE)

closures$last_date <- closures$date

trip.level <- merge(closures,trip.level, by = "last_date", all.y=TRUE)

simpleDID.trip.lm <- lm(revenue_trip ~ PMNM_dummy + high_post + high_effort, data = trip.level)
